msgid ""
"To dual-boot |trueos| with an existing operating system, first make sure "
"there is either a free partition or an area of free space to use. For "
"example, if the system is currently running a Windows operating system, it "
"usually occupies the entire hard drive. The partition with the current "
"operating system will need to shrink to make room to install |trueos|. "
"Shrinking is an operation that retains the current operating system while "
"reducing the size of its partition. This section demonstrates how to create "
"free space within Windows 10."
